<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-27T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Stettinius Mission/73:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-27T17:00:00+02:00">April
                                        27, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 27—3:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3446. Deles 36. From the Under Secretary. I discussed the question of
                                Iran yesterday with Eden and the Soviet Ambassador, on the lines
                                indicated in Deles number 22, April 19, after Murray and Sir Maurice
                                had paved the way by a similar talk with the Counselor of the Soviet
                                Embassy. The Soviet reaction was favorable in both instances and the
                                Ambassador is telegraphing Moscow as requested.</p>
                            <p>I suggest that appropriate instructions be sent to Ford without delay
                                and that Moscow be informed of these developments.<note n="65" xml:id="d333fn65">Repeated in paraphrase in telegram 261, April
                                    28, 5 p.m., to Tehran, and in telegram 1058, 5 p.m., to
                                    Moscow.</note> The British are telegraphing their
                                representatives at Tehran and Moscow today. [Stettinius.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>